The paper discusses the use of electromagnetic side-channel analysis for digital forensic investigations on IoT devices. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) since IoT devices often communicate with each other. The paper also touches on the privacy and usability aspects of user data, which could fall under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the technique for digital investigations, which could fall under the category of cybercrime (cs.CY).
